title: Statement by the Press Secretary on H.R. 3325 & S.J.Res. 9 | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House




September 18, 2009

 



Statement by the Press Secretary on H.R. 3325 & S.J.Res. 9




 THE WHITE HOUSE Office of the Press Secretary  ___________________________________________________________________________  For Immediate Release                                                 September 18, 2009 STATEMENT BY THE PRESS SECRETARY   On Friday, September 18, 2009, the President signed into law: H.R. 3325, which extends for one year the Social Security Administration’s Work Incentives Planning and Assistance program and Protection and Advocacy for Beneficiaries of Social Security program; and S.J.Res. 9, which appoints France A. Cordova as a citizen regent of the Board of Regents of the Smithsonian Institution.
